TEXT.0: Precipitating electrons and ions observed at nominally 850km altitude and over a range of energies from 30 eV to 30 keV using the Special Sensor J (SSJ) instrument.  Please contact Rob.Redmon@noaa.gov with questions and comments. Many individuals made important contributions including: D. Hardy, E. Holeman, F. Rich, D. Ober, G. Wilson, J. Machuzak, K. Kadinsky-Cade, J. McGarity, W.F. Denig, K. Martin, R. Redmon, D. Knipp, L. Kilcommons.

Logical_source_description.0: Precipitating electrons and ions observed at nominally 850km.

Rules_of_use.0: Please acknowledge providers.  If you find problems, please report them.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Earth Centered Inertial (ECI) spacecraft location (x,y,z) in km.

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Epoch is True of Date (TOD). These ECI coordinates are calculated from an SPDF SSC Locator 1-minute ephemeris using an 8 order interpolation (Burden, R. L. and Faires, J. D., Numerical Analysis, 5th Ed., PWS Publishing Company, Boston, 1993). Using SPDF methods, expected accuracy is on the order of a few km.
Calculated using IDL Astro Library function eci2geo().
Calculated using IDL Astro Library function eci2geo().

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Distance from center of Earth in km.

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Calculated using SuperDARN AACGM IDL library. Values are the result of linearly interpolating between 2 nearest AACGM 5-year epochs.
Calculated using SuperDARN AACGM IDL library. Values are the result of linearly interpolating between 2 nearest AACGM 5-year epochs.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Altitude Adjusted Corrected Geomagnetic Local Time

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Calculated using SuperDARN AACGM IDL library. Values are the result of linearly interpolating between 2 nearest AACGM 5-year epochs.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Electron counts as observed; no corrections.

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: This instrument doesn't have a dedicated background channel. An estimate is arrived at by running the AFRL technique forward and backward in time and choosing the largest of these two estimates for each second and energy channel.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Estimated uncertainty in electron differential energy flux (ev/cm2/delta-eV/ster/s).
Electron total energy flux integrated over energy (eV/cm2/ster/s).
Estimated uncertainty in electron total energy flux integrated over energy (eV/cm2/ster/s).

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Computed as: Total Energy Flux / Total Number Flux

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Estimated uncertainty in average electron energy (eV).
Ion counts as observed; no corrections.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Estimated uncertainty in ion differential energy flux (ev/cm2/delta-eV/ster/s).
